ğŸŒ± Relationship Between Spring & Spring Boot
| Term                 | Meaning                                                                            |
| -------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Spring Framework** | Core framework providing IoC, DI, AOP, MVC, Security, etc.                         |
| **Spring Boot**      | A **framework built on top of Spring Framework** to simplify configuration & setup |
ğŸ” Why the Confusion Happens

People often say â€œSpring Boot Frameworkâ€ because:
Spring itself is a framework
Boot adds automation, defaults, and tooling
So they casually append the word framework
But officially, the name is just Spring Boot.

ğŸ§  Key Point for Interviews

â“ Is Spring Boot and Spring Boot framework same?
âœ… Yes. Spring Boot itself is a framework built on top of the Spring Framework.

You can also say:
â€œSpring Boot is an opinionated framework that simplifies Spring application development.â€

ğŸ†š Spring Framework vs Spring Boot (Quick)
| Aspect           | Spring Framework | Spring Boot         |
| ---------------- | ---------------- | ------------------- |
| Configuration    | Manual           | Auto-configured     |
| Setup            | Complex          | Very fast           |
| Server           | External         | Embedded            |
| Boilerplate      | High             | Minimal             |
| Production Ready | Extra setup      | Built-in (Actuator) |


ğŸŒ± Spring vs Spring Boot
1ï¸âƒ£ Spring Framework

Spring is a core Java framework that provides infrastructure support for building enterprise applications.

2ï¸âƒ£ Spring Boot

Spring Boot is a framework built on top of Spring that simplifies development by providing auto-configuration, embedded servers, and production-ready features.

ğŸ”¹ What is Spring?

Spring focuses on flexibility and control.

Main Features:

Inversion of Control (IoC)
Dependency Injection (DI)
AOP (Aspect-Oriented Programming)
Spring MVC (Web)
Spring JDBC / ORM / JPA
Spring Security
Spring Transactions

Characteristics:

Manual configuration (XML / Java / annotations)
External application server required (Tomcat, JBoss)
More boilerplate code
More control, less opinionated

ğŸ”¹ What is Spring Boot?

Spring Boot focuses on simplicity and speed.
Main Features:
Auto-configuration
Starter dependencies
Embedded servers (Tomcat by default)
Production-ready tools (Actuator)
Opinionated defaults

Characteristics:

Minimal configuration
No need for external server
Faster project setup
Ideal for microservices & REST APIs

ğŸ†š Spring vs Spring Boot (Comparison Table)
| Feature          | Spring            | Spring Boot                |
| ---------------- | ----------------- | -------------------------- |
| Type             | Core framework    | Framework on top of Spring |
| Configuration    | Manual            | Auto-configured            |
| Server           | External required | Embedded                   |
| Boilerplate      | More              | Very less                  |
| Startup Time     | Slower            | Faster                     |
| Microservices    | Complex           | Best choice                |
| Production Tools | Manual            | Built-in (Actuator)        |

ğŸ§  Interview One-Line Answers

What is Spring?
ğŸ‘‰ Spring is a Java framework that provides core infrastructure like IoC, DI, AOP, and transaction management.

What is Spring Boot?
ğŸ‘‰ Spring Boot is a framework built on top of Spring that simplifies application development using auto-configuration and embedded servers.

Is Spring Boot replacing Spring?
ğŸ‘‰ âŒ No. Spring Boot uses Spring internally.

Can Spring Boot work without Spring?
ğŸ‘‰ âŒ No. Spring Boot depends on Spring Framework.

âœ… When to Use What?
Use Spring:
Legacy enterprise applications
When fine-grained configuration control is needed
XML-heavy existing systems

Use Spring Boot:
New applications
REST APIs & microservices
Cloud-native applications
Faster development & deployment

ğŸ”‘ Final Summary

Spring provides features. Spring Boot makes them easy to use.
